        "title": "Comparing: parempi, kivempi, paras",
        "summary": "Comparatives end in -mpi: parempi (better), halvempi (cheaper), kivempi (nicer). In speech 'kuin' (than) shrinks to 'ku', and vowels shift: nopeampi → nopeempi. Superlatives: paras (best), suosituin (most popular).",
        "examples": [
            "Tää on parempi ku toi. = This is better than that.",
            "Kumpi on halvempi? = Which one is cheaper?",
            "Mitä nopeempi, sen parempi. = The faster the better."
        ]
    },
